        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 6:30PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 629 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Craig Springs, or near Paint Bank, moving west at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Pembroke...
Union...
New Castle...
Mountain Lake...
Paint Bank...
Sinking Creek...
and Laurel Branch.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
